Titolo: Akatsuki Blitzkampf

Anno: 2007

Descrizione: Akatsuki Blitzkampf (アカツキ電光戦記, Akatsuki Denkō Senki, Akatsuki Chronicles) (also known as Akatsuki/En-Eins (アカツキ/エンアイン, Akatsuki/En-Ain)) is a series of Japanese dōjin 2D fighting games, developed by the dōjin circle SUBTLE STYLE for Microsoft Windows. The first installment in the series, titled Akatsuki Shisei Ichigō (アカツキ試製一號, lit. Akatsuki Prototyp 1, Akatsuki Prototype 1) was released in November 2003. It would later be reworked and released as Akatsuki Blitzkampf on April 30, 2007. On September 27, 2007 Japanese video game magazine Monthly Arcadia revealed that the game would be launched as an arcade title, published by SUBTLE STYLE itself.  The arcade version of the game was titled Akatsuki Blitzkampf Ausf. Achse, and was released february 20, 2008 for the Sega NAOMI arcade system. On march 26th of 2010 the game was announced to be getting a PC port, which was later released as En-Eins Perfektewelt (エヌアイン完全世界, En-Ain Kanzen Sekai, En-Eins Perfect World) in 2011.

